<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 07 at 2:55AM EDT until May 07 at 3:30AM EDT by NWS Indianapolis</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 330 AM EDT
FOR NORTHERN MADISON...NORTHEASTERN HAMILTON AND SOUTHEASTERN TIPTON
COUNTIES...
At 255 AM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Elwood, or 13
miles northwest of Anderson, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Frankton, Orestes, Alexandria and Summitville.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
